  "text": "[14] A zone characterized by both indefinite s 1 orientations and small R-values was found in the location of a low-V p and high-conductivity anomaly beneath the mainshock hypocenter (Figures 3b and 3c ). This anomaly hints at the presence of crustal fluids [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , which may be influencing the stress field in the source region.",
